AMM

14 June, 2017

Friedman 1

  • \[X_{1}, \cdots,X_{9} \sim U(0,1)\]
  • \[ Y= 10 \sin(\pi X_1\ast X_2)+20(X_{3}-.5)^2+10X_4+5X_{5}+\epsilon\]
  • \[ \epsilon \sim N(0,1)\]

For each we have a training set of size 250 and a test set of size 1000.

There are 500 simulations performed.
